<br>
Look...do you realize how many people you are potentially talking about being involved in these raids?<br>
<br>
Who is going to keep track of who has what, and who got what?<br>
<br>
It's not a job I would wish on my worst enemy.<br>
<br>
I agree that the raid planners and pullers should get a piece of the pie: perhaps the option of calling a specific item, or cash loot, their choice. I don't think anyone will disagree with you there.<br>
<br>
But most importantly, we're raiding to have fun...right?<br>
<br>
Right guys? I mean...how much of a job do you want this to be?<br>
<br>
If you want to organize a small raid and set forth specific rules to govern it, there is no obstacle standing in your way.<br>
<br>
Again though I'd like to point out why I think the merit system wont work for us, the SGA, as a whole:<br>
<br>
1.) We are too large--administration nightmare<br>
2.) We were  formed as an alternative for the casual player to participate in raids...without havoing to attend them five times a week.<br>
<br>
In most cases I'd believe in a merit system. In the case of the SGA I predict it wont work. Be happy to be proven wrong though, but don't think I am. <p><b> ~The Nightblind Bard~
